DIGEST
SB 433 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Boudreaux
Proposed law requires Medicaid coverage for FDA-approved weight loss medications that
are medically necessary and prescribed by a licensed healthcare provider for Medicaid
recipients that meet the coverage criteria established by the La. Dept. of Health.
Proposed law allows prior authorization as determined by the department.
Proposed law prohibits step therapy requirements for coverage of the weight loss
medications.
Proposed law requires the department to implement weight loss coverage in a manner that
ensures fiscal sustainability consistent with federal requirements.
Proposed law provides that implementation of proposed law is subject to appropriation.
Effective January 1, 2027.
(Adds R.S. 46:460.38)
